ckButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528810\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jda1665702566611.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jda1665702566611.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jda1665702566611.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jda1665702566611\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Reconnect Process for New Occurrences\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jda1665702566611__section_n3d_lf3_mcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1057870e54\">No Database Connection</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jda1665702566611__p_d44240e1_d44241e1_d44242e1\">Uniface does the following for all disconnected\n            occurrences with modification status <code class=\"ph codeph\">new</code> and no connection to the\n            database:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"jda1665702566611__ol_h23_tg3_mcc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Uniface searches for the occurrence in the component using the disconnected\n               occurrence Id. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If the occurrence exists in the component, the reconnect process continues at step\n               4. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If the occurrence does not exist in the component, Uniface recreates the occurrence\n               using the same disconnected occurrence Id. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Field data is copied from the disconnected occurrence.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Occurrence modification flags are set to New (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occmod</span>=1,\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$storetype</span>=1). </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Field modification flags are set to Modified (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldmod</span>=1). </li>\n<li class=\"li\">The disconnected occurrence is deleted, and the reconnect process continues with the\n               next disconnected occurrence. </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jda1665702566611__section_zlw_dh3_mcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1057870e100\">With Database Connection</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jda1665702566611__p_d44246e1_d44247e1_d44248e1\">Uniface does the following for all disconnected\n            occurrences with modification status <code class=\"ph codeph\">new</code> and a connection to the\n            database:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"jda1665702566611__ol_xsp_lh3_mcc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Uniface searches for the occurrence in the component using the disconnected\n               occurrence Id. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If the occurrence exists in the component, the reconnect process continues at step\n               4. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If the occurrence does not exist in the component, Uniface recreates the occurrence\n               using the same disconnected occurrence Id. Uniface does not search for the occurrence\n               in the database. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Field data is copied from the disconnected occurrence. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Occurrence modification flags are set to New (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$occmod=1</code>,\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">$storetype=1</code>). </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Field modification flags are set to Modified (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$fieldmod=1</code>).</li>\n<li class=\"li\">The disconnected occurrence is deleted, and the reconnect process continues with the\n               next disconnected occurrence.<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"jda1665702566611__note_oxb_h33_mcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> After the reconnect process, key validation should be\n                     used to check for duplicate keys in the database.</div>\n</div></li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eai1665702600334.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occmod</a><p>Return the modification status of an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjy1665702601052.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldmod</a><p>Return the modification status of a field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/znp1665702699570.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$storetype</a><p>Return the type of update for the current occurrence.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528810\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528810\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Reconnect Process for New Occurrences Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Reconnect Process for New Occurrences No Database Connection Uniface does the following for all disconnected occurrences with modification status new and no connection to the database: Uniface searches for the occurrence in the component using the disconnected occurrence Id. If the occurrence exists in the component, the reconnect process continues at step 4. If the occurrence does not exist in the component, Uniface recreates the occurrence using the same disconnected occurrence Id. Field data is copied from the disconnected occurrence. Occurrence modification flags are set to New ( $occmod =1, $storetype =1). Field modification flags are set to Modified ( $fieldmod =1). The disconnected occurrence is deleted, and the reconnect process continues with the next disconnected occurrence. With Database Connection Uniface does the following for all disconnected occurrences with modification status new and a connection to the database: Uniface searches for the occurrence in the component using the disconnected occurrence Id. If the occurrence exists in the component, the reconnect process continues at step 4. If the occurrence does not exist in the component, Uniface recreates the occurrence using the same disconnected occurrence Id. Uniface does not search for the occurrence in the database. Field data is copied from the disconnected occurrence. Occurrence modification flags are set to New ( $occmod=1 , $storetype=1 ). Field modification flags are set to Modified ( $fieldmod=1 ). The disconnected occurrence is deleted, and the reconnect process continues with the next disconnected occurrence. Note: After the reconnect process, key validation should be used to check for duplicate keys in the database. Related Links $occmod Return the modification status of an occurrence. $fieldmod Return the modification status of a field. $storetype Return the type of update for the current occurrence. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}